Get the current state of a zone including its desired and current temperature. Check out the example output for more.

Parameters:
  zone (int): The zone ID.

Returns:
  (dict): A dictionary with the current settings and sensor measurements of the zone.

??? info "Result example"
    ```json
    {
      "activityDataPoints": {
        "heatingPower": {
          "percentage": 0.0,
          "timestamp": "2017-02-21T11:56:52.204Z",
          "type": "PERCENTAGE"
        }
      },
      "geolocationOverride": False,
      "geolocationOverrideDisableTime": None,
      "link": {
        "state": "ONLINE"
      },
      "overlay": None,
      "overlayType": None,
      "preparation": None,
      "sensorDataPoints": {
        "humidity": {
          "percentage": 44.0,
          "timestamp": "2017-02-21T11:56:45.369Z",
          "type": "PERCENTAGE"
        },
        "insideTemperature": {
          "celsius": 18.11,
          "fahrenheit": 64.6,
          "precision": {
            "celsius": 1.0,
            "fahrenheit": 1.0
          },
          "timestamp": "2017-02-21T11:56:45.369Z",
          "type": "TEMPERATURE"
        }
      },
      "setting": {
        "power": "ON",
        "temperature": {
          "celsius": 20.0,
          "fahrenheit": 68.0
        },
        "type": "HEATING"
      },
      "tadoMode": "HOME"
    }
    ```

